divs: sighting detailsi was leaving work going south on us 41\27 at approximatley 6:30 pm on 11\04\2012. i was actually looking for the space station which shows up brightly in the florida night sky. i got past a field of trees when something caught my eye in the southwest sky. it was orange\red in color moving horizontally across the sky. my first thought, of course was that it was a plane. i quickly noted that there was not any other lights. then i thought maybe it was a meteor or shooting star but there was not a tail so it always be obvious it was not either of these. the object was orange\red in color and elongated in shape but not quite oval. it moved rapidly across the sky. there was absolutely no sound whatsoever. i watched it for 2-3 possibly 4 minutes then it was simply gone. there 1 minute gone the next.
Summary: Saw red/orange orb in sky moving horizontally. It just blinked out in 2-3 min
